  "excerpt": "Ok, this year is flying. So glad I am doing/enjoying/keeping up with Project Life. Here is how Week 7 went down. In case you were hoping for a cleaner desk (spoiler alert), that happens in Week 8. Got a couple…",
  "legacyPath": "/blog/2012/02/project-life-week-7",
  "legacyFile": "blog__2012__02__project-life-week-7.html",
  "imageCount": 9,
  "body": "<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243463945-46T97VW1UC78TIM4OTU3/image-asset.jpeg\"/>\n\n\n</figure>\n\n\n<p>Ok, this year is flying. So glad I am doing/enjoying/keeping up with Project Life. Here is how Week 7 went down. In case you were hoping for a cleaner desk (spoiler alert), that happens in Week 8. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243481089-YXM3ZTOK6R2QID2B1NIF/17b-desk.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>Got a couple sweet Valentine's cards from friends and couldn't resist putting them in. They might be my favorite parts of this week.  </p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243494155-TTSDUQDE97BBA4UAMG38/17c-11.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>The Pep Boys card was too cute, I had to put it in here instead of my keychain. I used <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/american-crafts/121139-amy-tangerine-large-letter-remarks-stickers/%3Ffilters%3D_amy%2Btangerine_\">these alphabets</a> on that card. The Currents and Coffee cards are <a href=\"http://lifelovepaper.com/blog/index.php/2012/02/1340/\">free downloads</a> from <a href=\"http://lifelovepaper.com/blog/\">Tina of LifeLovePaper</a>. I printed them onto kraft cardstock instead of white, mainly just to try to be a little different. Digging how it turned out. Thanks Tina for sharing the love! </p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243509780-8T7A59AS56ZLDGCCYTFF/17d-24.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p>The Play card is from <a href=\"http://www.jamaicamakes.com/\">Jamaica</a>. I stamped the airplane from <a href=\"http://www.shareasale.com/r.cfm?u=530666&amp;b=199868&amp;m=24698&amp;afftrack=lovestruck&amp;urllink=www%2Esimonsaysstamp%2Ecom%2Fservlet%2Fthe%2D36752%2F59151%2DLOVESTRUCK%2DLOVE%2DSTRUCK%2FDetail\">the LoveStruck stamp set</a> right onto it and used the highly coveted <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/american-crafts/124456-dear-lizzy-neapolitan-roller-date-stamp/%3Ffilters%3D_dear%2Blizzy%2Bdate%2Bstamp_%252Fstamps\">Dear Lizzy date stamp</a> as well.</p><p>I didn't take too many photos when I taught at <a href=\"http://www.scrapbookers-dream.com/index.html\">Scrapbooker's Dream</a>, but here are some others. It was so nice to have women driving in from different states!  </p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n\n\n<img alt=\"17e-scrapbookersdream2.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243557844-3MU4QP3H25WRJ8A1UZ2I/17e-scrapbookersdream2.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"17f-32.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243558317-BYE8488XXBW41CE1992F/17f-32.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"17g-42.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243559504-Z7MFLYD6TJTZJZ1UQQ2G/17g-42.jpg\">\n</img>\n\n<img alt=\"17h-52.jpg\" src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243559884-3RU2K9N89MMTFFH433TK/17h-52.jpg\"/>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Can't emphasize how much I am loving <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/mn/search/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;x=0&amp;tag=wwwamytangeri-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;y=0&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;field-keywords=project%20life&amp;url=search-alias%3Daps\">Project Life</a>. It gives all the little things I collect a nice home, which is just what I need because I have trouble throwing stuff away. Plus, not all of the events of my life need to be documented (on its own scrapbook page), so this gives me a good excuse to put in what I want, no matter how trivial. And I am not calling Haagen-Dazs Caramel Cone ice cream trivial. It is a little slice of heaven in a cup. You can see all my Project Life posts <a href=\"http://amytangerine.blogspot.com/search/label/project%20life\">here</a>.</p><p>*************************</p><p>As promised, for the spot in Shimelle's <a href=\"http://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=cl&amp;mi=10513&amp;pw=41735&amp;url=http%3A//www.twopeasinabucket.com/shop/two-peas/125203-the-hitchhikers-guide-to-scrapbooking-workshop/\">Hitchhiker's Guide to Scrapbooking</a>... </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<figure>\n\n\n<img src=\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5dd0ae59b4b4b35c07faf907/1605243595616-NO9Q2MGOQSH5PHUD783R/17i-2pswinner2.jpg\"/>\n\n\n<figcaption>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.blogger.com/profile/08341721539412808566\">Nora</a>  said...</p><p>Wow, love your layout and the ones you shared as well!:) twopeasuser: noraraaum</p><p>Thanks to those who entered and I hope everyone has a wonderful weekend! </p>\n</figcaption>\n</figure>"
}